and Psychiatry</em>, 26(5): 533&ndash;548.
doi:10.1016/S0160-2527(03)00085-2</li>

<li>Tan, Jacinta O. A., Anne Stewart, Raymond Fitzpatrick, and Tony
Hope, 2010, &ldquo;Attitudes of Patients with Anorexia Nervosa to
Compulsory Treatment and Coercion&rdquo;, <em>International Journal of
Law and Psychiatry</em>, 33(1): 13&ndash;19.
doi:10.1016/j.ijlp.2009.10.003</li>

<li>Taylor, Shelley E. and Jonathon D. Brown, 1988, &ldquo;Illusion
and Well-Being: A Social Psychological Perspective on Mental
Health&rdquo;, <em>Psychological Bulletin</em>, 103(2): 193&ndash;210.
doi:10.1037/0033-2909.103.2.193</li>

<li>Tekin, &#350;erife, 2011, &ldquo;Self-Concept Through the
Diagnostic Looking Glass: Narratives and Mental Disorder&rdquo;,
<em>Philosophical Psychology</em>, 24(3): 357&ndash;380.
doi:10.1080/09515089.2011.559622</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2016, &ldquo;Are Mental Disorders Natural
Kinds?: A Plea for a New Approach to Intervention in
Psychiatry&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy, Psychiatry, &amp; Psychology</em>,
23(2): 147&ndash;163. doi:10.1353/ppp.2016.0013</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2019, &ldquo;The Missing Self in Scientific
Psychiatry&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>, 196: 2197&ndash;2215.
doi:10.1007/s11229-017-1324-0</li>

<li>Tekin, &#350;erife and Robyn Bluhm (eds.), 2019, <em>The
Bloomsbury Companion to the Philosophy of Psychiatry</em>, London:
Bloomsbury Academic.</li>

<li>Thornicroft, Graham, 2006, <em>Shunned: Discrimination against
People with Mental Illness</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>Thornton, Tim, 2007, <em>Essential Philosophy of Psychiatry</em>,
Oxford: Oxford University Press.
doi:10.1093/med/9780199228713.001.1</li>

<li>Tsou, Jonathan Y., 2007, &ldquo;Hacking on the Looping Effects of
Psychiatric Classifications: What is an Interactive and Indifferent
Kind?&rdquo;, <em>International Studies in the Philosophy of
Sciencec</em>, 21(3): 329&ndash;344. doi:10.1080/02698590701589601</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2015, &ldquo;DSM-5 and Psychiatry&rsquo;s
Second Revolution: Descriptive vs. Theoretical Approaches to
Psychiatric Classification&rdquo;, in Steeves Demazeux and Patrick
