doi:10.1185/03007995.2011.653436</li>

<li>Washington, Natalia, 2016, &ldquo;Culturally Unbound:
Cross-Cultural Cognitive Diversity and the Science of
Psychopathology&rdquo;, <em>Philosophy, Psychiatry, &amp;
Psychology</em>, 23(3): 165&ndash;179.</li>

<li>Watson, Gary, 2004, <em>Agency and Answerability: Selected
Essays</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199272273.001.0001</li>

<li>West, Robert, 2006, <em>Theory of Addiction</em>, Oxford:
Blackwell.</li>

<li>Westin, Anna, 2020, <em>An Existential Phenomenology of
Addiction</em>. London: Bloomsbury Press.</li>

<li>Whitaker, Robert and Lisa Cosgrove, 2015, <em>Psychiatry under the
Influence: Institutional Corruption, Social Injury and Prescriptions
for Reform</em>, New York: Palgrave Macmillan.</li>

<li>[WHO] World Health Organization, 2020, <em>The ICD-11
Classification of Mental and Behavioural Disorders</em>, Geneva: World
Health Organization.</li>

<li>Wickham, Sophie and Richard Bentall, 2016, &ldquo;Are Specific
Early-Life Adversities Associated With Specific Symptoms of
